<section id="overview">
      <h2>Year Overview</h2>
      <p>The Goat (<span class="chinese-char">羊</span>) occupies the Earthly Branch <strong>Wei (未)</strong>, carrying Yin Earth energy with hidden Fire and Wood. In 2026, the Goat enjoys one of the zodiac's most harmonious relationships: the <strong>Wu-Wei Liu He</strong> (午未合) — a secret friend bond with the Horse year.</p>
      <p>This Liu He combination means the year's energy actively <strong>supports and nurtures</strong> the Goat. Fire generates Earth in the productive cycle, and the Horse-Goat bond adds an emotional warmth and collaborative spirit. Where other signs may struggle with the Fire Horse's intensity, the Goat finds it comforting and energising.</p>
      <p>The Goat's natural creativity, compassion, and aesthetic sensitivity are highlighted. 2026 is a year to <strong>express, create, and connect</strong>. The Goat's often-underestimated strengths receive recognition, and supportive allies appear in both professional and personal spheres.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="career">
      <h2>Career &amp; Finance</h2>
      <p>The Liu He support creates <strong>favourable career conditions</strong>. The Goat's talents — creativity, diplomacy, attention to beauty and detail — are in demand. Collaborative projects succeed, and the Goat's contributions are recognised by authority figures who may have previously overlooked them.</p>
      <p><strong>Finance</strong> improves through the Fire-Earth productive cycle. Income grows steadily through the year, with opportunities for additional earnings from creative side projects, consulting, or artistic commissions. The Goat's natural frugality serves well — resist the temptation to splurge when income rises.</p>
      <p><strong>Best sectors:</strong> Arts, design, fashion, culinary arts, healthcare, counselling, education, non-profit work, and any field requiring empathy and aesthetic judgment.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="love">
      <h2>Love &amp; Relationships</h2>
      <p>The Horse-Goat Liu He makes 2026 one of the <strong>best years for the Goat's love life</strong>. The secret friend energy creates warmth, understanding, and natural compatibility with potential partners. Existing relationships deepen as the Goat feels secure enough to be vulnerable and expressive.</p>
      <p><strong>Single Goats</strong> have excellent prospects. The year's energy attracts partners who appreciate the Goat's gentle, creative nature rather than expecting aggressive pursuit. Connections formed in artistic or cultural settings are particularly promising. The Rabbit and Pig months (March and November) complete the Wood triangle and bring additional romantic energy.</p>
      <p><strong>Family harmony</strong> is strong. The Goat's nurturing energy is amplified, making this an excellent year for strengthening family bonds, hosting gatherings, and creating a beautiful home environment.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="health">
      <h2>Health &amp; Wellness</h2>
      <p>The Goat's health outlook is <strong>generally positive</strong> in 2026. Fire's warming energy supports the Goat's sometimes fragile constitution, improving circulation, digestion, and energy levels. The risk of excess Earth (dampness, weight gain, lethargy) should be managed through regular movement and balanced diet.</p>
      <p><strong>Digestive health</strong> benefits from warm, cooked foods and regular meal times. Avoid excessive cold or raw foods, especially during the summer months when Fire is strongest. The spleen (Earth organ) functions best with consistent, moderate nourishment.</p>
      <p>Creative activities serve as both <strong>mental health support and physical therapy</strong>. Art, music, gardening, cooking, and crafts help the Goat process emotions and maintain equilibrium. Time in nature, particularly gardens and pastoral settings, is deeply restorative.</p>
    </section>

